At 02:09 PM 12/22/2003, Richard Atwell wrote:
>When looking for a mechanical oil pressure gauge, is 60 psi enough or is 100 psi better?

You will exceed 60psi when cold.  Get the 100psi gauge if you have to choose between those two.  I have an 0-80psi electrical gauge and the range is just right.  Are you really going to run a hose all the way to the front?

-David
